      "content": "\u003cdiv class\u003d\"introduction img-head\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class\u003d\"header\"\u003e\n    \u003cimg src\u003d\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,\u003d\u003d\" alt\u003d\"App Icon\" /\u003e\n    \u003ch3\u003eWelcome to the Open Role Tracker \u003c/h3\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\n  \u003csection\u003e\n    \u003ch4\u003eOverview\u003c/h4\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003e\n      An advanced GenAI-powered lead generation tool that helps you discover, extract, enrich, and score companies hiring for a specific job title in a given location. The system is powered by Serper search API, and a modular workflow architecture.\n    \u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/section\u003e\n\n  \u003csection\u003e\n    \u003ch4\u003eInput\u003c/h4\u003e\n    \u003cul\u003e\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eJob Title\u003c/strong\u003e (required): The exact role you\u0027re targeting (e.g., “Data Scientist”)\u003c/li\u003e\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eLocation\u003c/strong\u003e (required): The geographic location to find hiring companies (e.g., “Mumbai”)\u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003c/ul\u003e\n  \u003c/section\u003e\n\n  \u003csection\u003e\n    \u003ch4\u003eOutput\u003c/h4\u003e\n    \u003cul\u003e\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eCompany Name:\u003c/strong\u003e Name of the hiring company\u003c/li\u003e\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eLocation:\u003c/strong\u003e Matches user input exactly\u003c/li\u003e\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eJob Title:\u003c/strong\u003e Matches user input exactly\u003c/li\u003e\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eSource Url:\u003c/strong\u003e Direct link to the job or company careers page\u003c/li\u003e\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e \u003cstrong\u003escore:\u003c/strong\u003e Value from 0–100 based on relevance, reputation, and completeness\u003c/li\u003e\n      \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e Output is returned as HTML table sorted by score\u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003c/ul\u003e\n  \u003c/section\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n",
